    "attributes": {
        "action": "UK Government to initiate another EU referendum immediately.",
        "additional_details": "This referendum will allow participants to chose ONE (and only one) of the following options:-\r\na) Leave the EU on the terms negotiated by Boris Johnson\r\nb) Leave the EU on the terms negotiated by Theresa May\r\nc) Leave the EU without an agreement\r\nd) Remain in the EU on established terms\r\nThe result to be decided by a simple majority of votes cast.\r\n\r\nThis referendum, run on the basis of a simple majority, offers a fair way out of the mess we got into by having a simple majority EU referendum in 2016.",
        "background": "UK Government to take the following steps immediately:-\r\n1. Ask the EU for an extension to article 50 to allow for another UK referendum\r\n2. Launch another EU referendum along the lines detailed below",
